# Git commit messages (this repository)

When proposing or running `git commit` for this repo:

- Use **[Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/)**-style subjects: `type(scope): imperative description` (see types below). Scope is optional; use a crate or area when it helps (`shahanshahi`, `ci`, `spec`, …).
- **Subject:** imperative mood, **~50–72 characters**, **no trailing period**, lowercase after the colon unless a proper noun.
- **Body:** optional blank line, then *what* / *why* (not a line-by-line diff). Wrap near **72 columns**. Link issues with `Fixes #n` / `See #n` when relevant.
- **One logical change per commit** when practical.
- **Breaking changes:** `!` after type/scope and/or a `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer describing user impact.
- **Never** add tool-attribution trailers (`Co-authored-by:` for bots, `Made-with:`, etc.) or `--trailer` marketing lines — see [`contributor-attribution.mdc`](./contributor-attribution.mdc).

**Types (match branch prefixes in [`CONTRIBUTING.md`](../../CONTRIBUTING.md)):** `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `test`, `refactor`, `chore`, `perf`, `build`, `ci`.

**Full guide:** [`docs/COMMIT_MESSAGES.md`](../../docs/COMMIT_MESSAGES.md).

**Do not** use `git commit --no-verify` or `git push --no-verify` unless the maintainer explicitly asks for a one-off bypass; let hooks run.
